er.com%2Fmoon-missions-why-astronauts-have-not-returned-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eastronauts%20to%20work%20and%20live%20on%20the%20moon%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20researchers%20want%20to%20use%20radar%20technology%20to%20identify%20even%20more%20caves%20under%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20ongoing%20effort%20to%20establish%20a%20permanent%20lunar%20base%20where%20humans%20can%20live%20and%20work%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20scientists%20have%20discovered%20a%20possible%20game%20changer%3A%20a%20large%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrance-group-spends-40-days-in-cave-with-no-clocks-or-sunlight-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderground%20cave%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20scientists%20have%20suspected%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-plans-three-moon-missions-after-discovering-new-lunar-mineral-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoon%20may%20harbor%3C%2Fa%3E%20caves%20below%20its%20surface.%20Now%2C%20a%20new%20paper%20from%20a%20team%20of%20Italian%20researchers%20offers%20the%20most%20convincing%20evidence%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLunar%20caves%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvanishing-radio-signals-mystery-objects-in-milky-way-galaxy-center-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremained%20a%20mystery%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20over%2050%20years.%20So%20it%20was%20exciting%20to%20be%20able%20to%20finally%20prove%20the%20existence%2C%26quot%3B%20authors%20Leonardo%20Carrer%20and%20Lorenzo%20Bruzzone%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Trento%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fmoon-caves-nasa-astronauts-2dc57751f41a6e24f377c2259e8668ba%23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20Associated%20Press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20speculates%20that%2C%20given%20how%20they%20think%20this%20cave%20formed%2C%20there%20could%20be%20hundreds%20more%20hidden%20under%20the%20lunar%20surface.%20Instead%20of%20building%20homes%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20we%20could%20inhabit%20the%20existing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmars-hole-whats-inside-possible-alien-life-home-for-astronauts-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaverns%20beneath%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b239c3e0-e708-4387-89f3-2e42feb7d927%5C%22%3EHow%20such%20a%20large%20cave%20formed%20on%20the%20moon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22photo%20of%20holes%20in%20gray%20moon%20surface%20where%20lava%20tubes%20collapsed%20in%20creating%20dark%20pits%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6696a8e15439fb59cebdd09d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221100%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20moon%20is%20covered%20in%20lava%20tubes%2C%20some%20of%20which%20have%20collapsed%20over%20time%20dotting%20the%20surface%20with%20deep%20pits.%20You%20can%20see%20here%20a%20lava%20tube%20on%20the%20right%20with%20multiple%20collapsed%20regions.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FGSFC%2FArizona%20State%20University%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJudging%20from%20the%20data%2C%20the%20researchers%20estimate%20the%20cave%20is%20approximately%20150%20feet%20wide%20and%20up%20to%20260%20feet%20long%2C%20which%20is%20slightly%20smaller%20than%20an%20American%20football%20field%20with%20the%20end%20zones%20cut%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-teenager-digs-underground-man-cave-after-fight-with-mom-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecave%20sits%20deep%20within%20a%20pit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20called%20the%20Mare%20Tranquillitatis%20pit%2C%20which%20likely%20formed%20when%20a%20lava%20tube%20collapsed.%20The%20moon%20has%20no%20active%20volcanoes%20today%2C%20but%20billions%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20its%20surface%20was%20covered%20with%20lava%20that%20flowed%20down%20and%20through%20valleys%2C%20carving%20tubes%20across%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20millennia%2C%20some%20of%20those%20tubes%20became%20unstable%20and%20collapsed%2C%20creating%20pits%2C%20like%20the%20one%20the%20research%20team%20studied%20from%20radar%20images%20taken%20by%20NASA's%20Lunar%20Reconnaissance%20Orbiter.%20We%20don't%20have%20a%20clear%20picture%20of%20what%20the%20caves%20look%20like%20inside%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhawaii-man-fell-into-lava-tube-died-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elava%20tubes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20those%20in%20Hawaii%2C%20can%20offer%20some%20idea.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA's%20LRO%20has%20identified%20over%20200%20of%20these%20pits%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20suggesting%20there%20could%20be%20hundreds%20of%20underground%20caves%2C%20too.%20These%20caves%20could%20offer%20future%20astronauts%20protection%20against%20the%20extreme%20conditions%20on%20the%20moon's%20surface%2C%20the%20researchers%20reported%20in%20the%20paper%20published%20Monday%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dab76d01862f993e378d2317fe347653ef82a817883bbe9fe8d9afce83885a42c%26postID%3D66968022c87a0f570985895c%26postSlug%3Dscientists-discover-underground-moon-cave-astronauts-could-live-2024-7%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41550-024-02302-y%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENature%20Astronomy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb3ecc6a-7871-4cb5-9860-0b7c7de2ed4d%5C%22%3EThe%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20living%20in%20moon%20caves%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22415%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22close%20up%20of%20a%20pit%20on%20the%20moon%20showing%20a%20shadowed%20region%20on%20the%20pit's%20bottom%20with%20loose%20debris%20lining%20the%20inside%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6696a98d5439fb59cebdd0f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22415%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPermanently%20shadowed%20regions%20inside%20lunar%20pits%20like%20Mare%20Tranquillitatis%2C%20shown%20here%2C%20could%20be%20a%20balmy%2063%20%C2%B0F.%3Cp%3ELunar%20Reconnaissance%20Orbiter%20Camera%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thick%20cave%20ceiling%20of%20rock%20is%20ideal%20to%20protect%20people%20and%20infrastructure%20from%20the%20wildly%20varying%20day-night%20lunar%20surface%20temperature%20variations%20and%20to%20block%20high%20energy%20radiation%20which%20bathes%20the%20lunar%20surface%2C%26quot%3B%20Katherine%20Joy%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20earth%20sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20with%20the%20study%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fjul%2F15%2Funderground-cave-found-on-moon-could-be-ideal-base-for-explorers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20moon%20has%20no%20atmosphere%20to%20help%20regulate%20climate%2C%20its%20surface%20sees%20drastic%20temperature%20swings.%20During%20the%20day%2C%20the%20sun's%20heat%20bakes%20the%20lunar%20surface%20to%20about%20250%20%C2%B0F%20and%20at%20night%20it%20can%20dip%20below%20-200%20%C2%B0F.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20underground%20caves%2C%20the%20temperature%20would%20be%20both%20consistent%20and%2C%20per%20past%20research%2C%20very%20comfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1029%2F2022GL099710%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20same%20region%20%E2%80%94%20Mare%20Tranquillitatis%20%E2%80%94%20a%20separate%20team%20of%20researchers%20used%20computer%20simulations%20to%20suggest%20that%20permanently%20shadowed%20regions%20within%20these%20lunar%20pits%2C%20and%20any%20adjacent%20caves%2C%20would%20remain%20at%20around%2063%20%C2%B0F.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReaching%20these%20pits%20and%20caves%20is%20another%20matter.%20The%20cave%20inside%20Mare%20Tranquillitatis%20is%20located%20over%20400%20feet%20from%20the%20surface%20near%20the%20bottom%20of%20a%20steep%20slope%20lined%20with%20loose%20debris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20up%20and%20down%20that%20slope%20would%20require%20some%20technological%20ingenuity%2C%20whether%20it's%20jet%20packs%20that%20can%20fly%20us%20in%20and%20out%2C%20some%20type%20of%20lunar%20elevator%20that%20can%20shuttle%20people%20up%20and%20down%2C%20or%20something%20else.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220f5166c7-ccb7-47f3-90eb-eaab140eb646%5C%22%3ETo%20the%20moon%20cave%20and%20beyond%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20person%20in%20a%20white%20spacesuit%20collects%20rocks%20on%20a%20mock%20up%20of%20the%20moon's%20surface%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6696d1488893442a515722ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExploring%20caves%20on%20the%20moon%20could%20offer%20a%20plethora%20of%20scientific%20data%20and%20resources%20for%20future%20space%20missions.%3Cp%3ECaspar%20Benson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERadar%20technology%20could%20help%20scientists%20identify%20even%20more%20caves%20and%20tubes%20extending%20from%20open%20pits%20on%20the%20moon's%20surface.%20In%20the%20future%2C%20a%20spacecraft%20with%20a%20higher-resolution%20radar%20could%20even%20map%20the%20interior%20of%20all%20the%20pits%20LRO%20has%20identified%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Nature%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20survey%26quot%3B%20would%20allow%20them%20to%20assess%20the%20best%20locations%20for%20further%20exploration%20and%20future%20moon%20bases%2C%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20chance%20that%20moon%20caves%20harbor%20water%2C%20which%20will%20be%20a%20crucial%20resource%20for%20any%20future%20moon%20bases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20long%20known%20there's%20frozen%20water%20on%20the%20moon%20%E2%80%94%20just%20under%20its%20surface%2C%20in%20its%20permanently%20shadowed%20craters%2C%20and%20even%20in%20lonely%20H2O%20molecules%20sprinkled%20across%20the%20sunlit%20lunar%20dirt%2C%20less%20moist%20than%20the%20Sahara%20Desert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20underground%20caves%20are%20shielded%20from%20the%20merciless%20vacuum%20of%20space%20and%20the%20radiation%20of%20the%20sun%2C%20they%20could%20have%20water%20ice%2C%20Bruzzone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2024-07-16%2Fcave-discovered-on-the-moon%2F104102032%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Australian%20Broadcasting%20Corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccess%20to%20lunar%20water%20is%20key%20to%20NASA's%20plans%20to%20establish%20a%20permanent%20base%20on%20the%20moon%20and%2C%20eventually%2C%20use%20it%20to%20hopscotch%20astronauts%20to%20Mars.%20Water%20wouldn't%20just%20be%20for%20drinking%3B%20it%20could%20also%20be%20broken%20down%20into%20its%20elementary%20components%20%E2%80%94%20hydrogen%20for%20rocket%20fuel%20and%20oxygen%20for%20breathing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBruzzone%20and%20his%20co-authors%20also%20noted%20that%20caves%20and%20lava%20tubes%20of%20different%20ages%20may%20act%20like%20fossilized%20records%20of%20the%20moon's%20history.%20Eventually%2C%20exploring%20them%20up%20close%20could%20help%20scientists%20better%20understand%20volcanic%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-discover-underground-moon-cave-astronauts-could-live-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721172618000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6696a8405439fb59cebdd03c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-discover-underground-moon-cave-astrona