usinessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-much-down-payment-for-a-house%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edown%20payment%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20a%20house%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3Cu%3E%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20your%20retirement%2C%20having%20a%20specific%20purpose%20for%20your%20savings%20can%20help%20you%20stay%20on%20track%20and%20maximize%20your%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAutomated%20savings%20helps%20to%20overcome%20the%20task%20of%20manual%20transfers%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20consistently%20contribute%20to%20your%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20a%20good%20plan%20is%20to%20set%20up%20an%20individual%20savings%20account%20for%20each%20savings%20goal%20(like%20an%20account%20for%20travel%2C%20emergency%20fund%2C%20or%20down%20payment)%20and%20then%20automate%20deposits%20to%20each%20account%20on%20payday.%20That%20ensures%20you're%20able%20to%20easily%20track%20where%20you%20are%20with%20each%20of%20your%20savings%20goals%20and%20makes%20it%20clear%20whether%20you%20should%20increase%20the%20amounts%20to%20each%20account%20based%20on%20your%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d938f4f0-79c9-4e8c-942c-e3b4bb8dfcb4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Avoiding%20the%20temptation%20to%20spend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20part%20about%20saving%20money%20is%20overcoming%20the%20temptation%20to%20dip%20into%20savings%20for%20non-essential%20purchases.%20This%20is%20where%20automating%20your%20savings%20can%20keep%20you%20on%20track.%20By%20setting%20up%20automated%20transfers%20to%20your%20savings%20account%2C%20you%20create%20a%20barrier%20between%20your%20discretionary%20income%20and%20the%20money%20you%20have%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20money%20is%20automatically%20transferred%20to%20your%20savings%2C%20it%20becomes%20a%20matter%20of%20out%20of%20sight%2C%20out%20of%20mind.%20You%20will%20now%20base%20your%20budget%20and%20spending%20based%20on%20the%20money%20that's%20left%20after%20the%20transfer%20happens.%20This%20makes%20you%20far%20less%20likely%20to%20dip%20into%20your%20would-be%20savings%20for%20a%20clothing%20sale%20or%20brunch%2C%20ensuring%20that%20your%20money%20stays%20where%20it%20belongs%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20bank%20and%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce3da795-567a-47df-8ac3-6a608b5a33bb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Taking%20advantage%20of%20compound%20interest%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESaving%20money%20isn't%20just%20about%20setting%20aside%20funds%20just%20to%20do%20it%3B%20it's%20also%20about%20making%20your%20money%20work%20for%20you%20and%20grow%20over%20time.%20A%20significant%20advantage%20of%20putting%20your%20savings%20on%20autopilot%20is%20the%20potential%20for%20consistent%20growth%20through%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20compounding%20effect%20increases%20the%20growth%20of%20your%20savings%20greatly%2C%20but%20it%20requires%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20right%20bank%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20there%20are%20numerous%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20offering%20APYs%20of%20up%20to%20almost%206%25%2C%20and%20many%20of%20these%20accounts%20come%20without%20deposit%20requirements%20or%20unnecessary%20fees.%20By%20taking%20advantage%20of%20the%20higher%20interest%20rates%20these%20accounts%20are%20offering%20and%20setting%20up%20automated%2C%20regular%20deposits%2C%20you%20can%20grow%20your%20money%20much%20faster%20than%20you%20would%20with%20just%20a%20regular%20saving